00:17:18.329 --> 00:17:23.496
Since we can't catch up on sleep,
what are we supposed to do?

00:17:23.496 --> 00:17:27.038
What do we do when we're, like,
tossing and turning in bed late at night

00:17:27.079 --> 00:17:30.121
or doing shift work or whatever else?

00:17:30.163 --> 00:17:32.496
MW: So you're right,
we can't catch up on sleep.

00:17:32.538 --> 00:17:33.829
Sleep is not like the bank.

00:17:33.871 --> 00:17:35.913
You can't accumulate a debt

00:17:35.913 --> 00:17:38.621
and then hope to pay it off
at a later point in time.

00:17:38.663 --> 00:17:41.788
I should also note the reason
that it's so catastrophic

00:17:41.829 --> 00:17:44.871
and that our health
deteriorates so quickly,

00:17:44.913 --> 00:17:47.621
first, it's because human beings
are the only species

00:17:47.663 --> 00:17:50.121
that deliberately deprive
themselves of sleep

00:17:50.163 --> 00:17:52.538
for no apparent reason.

00:17:52.579 --> 00:17:53.704
DB: Because we're smart.

00:17:53.746 --> 00:17:58.579
MW: And I make that point
because it means that Mother Nature,

00:17:58.579 --> 00:18:00.288
throughout the course of evolution,

00:18:00.288 --> 00:18:04.621
has never had to face the challenge
of this thing called sleep deprivation.

00:18:05.288 --> 00:18:08.704
So she's never developed a safety net,

00:18:08.746 --> 00:18:10.871
and that's why when you undersleep,

00:18:10.871 --> 00:18:15.204
things just sort of implode so quickly,
both within the brain and the body.

00:18:15.246 --> 00:18:17.996
So you just have to prioritize.

00:18:18.038 --> 00:18:21.329
DB: OK, but tossing and turning in bed,

00:18:21.371 --> 00:18:22.788
what do I do?

00:18:22.788 --> 00:18:27.413
MW: So if you are staying in bed
awake for too long,

00:18:27.454 --> 00:18:30.704
you should get out of bed
and go to a different room

00:18:30.704 --> 00:18:32.038
and do something different.

00:18:32.038 --> 00:18:36.371
The reason is because your brain
will very quickly associate your bedroom

00:18:36.413 --> 00:18:38.704
with the place of wakefulness,

00:18:38.746 --> 00:18:41.413
and you need to break that association.

00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:44.329
So only return to bed when you are sleepy,

00:18:44.371 --> 00:18:47.913
and that way you will relearn
the association that you once had,

00:18:47.954 --> 00:18:50.454
which is your bed is the place of sleep.

00:18:50.454 --> 00:18:52.121
So the analogy would be,

00:18:52.163 --> 00:18:55.746
you'd never sit at the dinner table,
waiting to get hungry,

00:18:55.746 --> 00:18:58.704
so why would you lie in bed,
waiting to get sleepy?

00:18:59.538 --> 00:19:01.538
DB: Well, thank you for that wake-up call.

00:19:01.579 --> 00:19:02.746
Great job, Matt.

